docs.abstract: James’s beard has gone gray since the season was suspended in March, but the Los Angeles Lakers forward was as dominant as ever in his first game of the restart on Thursday.
docs.snippet: James’s beard has gone gray since the season was suspended in March, but the Los Angeles Lakers forward was as dominant as ever in his first game of the restart on Thursday.
docs.lead_paragraph: LeBron James has seen a great deal during his 17 seasons in the N.B.A. He has already won three championships, and now aspires to win his first with the Los Angeles Lakers. At 35, he is one of the oldest players in the league, with patches of gray showing in the beard he grew out during the four months he recently spent in relative seclusion.

headline.main: LeBron James Still Reigns as the N.B.A. Returns
headline.print_headline: As the N.B.A. Returns From Its Hiatus, It’s Still King James’s Court

docs.abstract: A first-look deal between Colin Kaepernick and Disney includes a documentary series at ESPN that will be produced by Jemele Hill, who left the network two years ago.

docs.lead_paragraph: Colin Kaepernick and the Walt Disney Company announced a production deal Monday that will see the activist quarterback produce “scripted and unscripted stories that explore race, social injustice and the quest for equity” for the media giant’s various platforms, including ESPN.

headline.main: Kaepernick’s Deal With Disney Includes a Jemele Hill Project at ESPN
headline.print_headline: Kaepernick Signs a Production Deal With Disney to Explore Social Injustice
